                @* <p>@Html.Raw(@Model.NewsDetail.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p> *@
                <p>@Html.Raw(@Model.NewsSummary.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p>
                <p>Suzuki has expanded its V-Strom lineup with the launch of the all-new V-Strom 800DE, a mid-weight adventure motorcycle designed to tackle both on-road and off-road challenges. This new offering fills the gap between the V-Strom 650XT and the larger 1050 models, targeting riders seeking adventure and versatility.</p>
                <p>At the heart of the V-Strom 800DE is a 776cc parallel-twin engine that delivers a robust 83 PS at 8500 rpm and 78 Nm of torque at 6800 rpm. This engine promises a smooth and balanced performance, especially with its 270-degree crankshaft, which emulates the feel of a V-twin. The bike features a six-speed gearbox with constant mesh for seamless gear changes.</p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/latestnews/2024/nov/suzukiunveilstheallnewvstrom80deadventuremotorcycle/1.webp" alt="Suzuki Unveils the All-New V-Strom 800DE Adventure Motorcycle - 1" title="Suzuki Unveils the All-New V-Strom 800DE Adventure Motorcycle - 1" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>The V-Strom 800DE stands out with its advanced electronics, including a Suzuki Intelligent Ride System (S.I.R.S.) with three riding modes (Active, Basic, Comfort), traction control, and a dedicated Gravel mode. The 5-inch TFT display provides clear information, while the adjustable windscreen and long-travel suspension enhance rider comfort.</p>
                <p>The bike’s rugged design incorporates a steel frame, 21-inch front and 17-inch rear spoke wheels, and 220mm ground clearance—ideal for off-road adventures. Dual-channel ABS, with a switchable rear system, ensures safety without compromising off-road control.</p>
                <p>In India, the V-Strom 800DE is expected to be priced around ₹10.30 lakhs (ex-showroom), positioning it against competitors like the Triumph Tiger 850 Sport and Yamaha Tenere 700.</p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/latestnews/2024/nov/suzukiunveilstheallnewvstrom80deadventuremotorcycle/2.webp" alt="Suzuki Unveils the All-New V-Strom 800DE Adventure Motorcycle - 2" title="Suzuki Unveils the All-New V-Strom 800DE Adventure Motorcycle - 2" /></div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Specifications & Features</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine:</span> 776cc, 4-stroke, 2-cylinder, liquid-cooled, DOHC</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Compression Ratio:</span> 12.8 : 1</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Front Tyre Size:</span> 90/90-21M/C 54H cross ply with tube</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Rear Tyre Size:</span> 150/70R17M/C 69H, radial with tube</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Transmission:</span> 6-speed constant mesh</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Suspension:</span> Long-travel fully adjustable front forks, rear mono-shock</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Electronics:</span> S.I.R.S., 3 riding modes, Gravel mode, traction control</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Display:</span> 5-inch TFT</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Ground Clearance:</span> 220mm</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
